<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheet/login.css">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
        integrity="sha384-EVSTQN3/azprG1Anm3QDgpJLIm9Nao0Yz1ztcQTwFspd3yD65VohhpuuCOmLASjC" crossorigin="anonymous">
</head>


<body>
    <%- include('../partials/flash') %>
        <div class="container mt-5">
            <div class="div me-4">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLabel" style="color: rgb(20, 37, 220);">
                    Authentication</h5>
                <ul>
                    This is how I manage Authentication:
                    <li class="ms-2 p-2"><small class="text-muted">
                            <ul> Duplication
                                <li class="mt-3">This ensures that each user has a unique username in the system.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </small></li>
                    <li class="ms-2 p-2"><small class="text-muted">
                            <ul> Model Requirements:
                                <li class="mt-3">The authentication process has specific requirements for the fields in
                                    the user
                                    model.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </small></li>
                    <li class="ms-2 p-2"><small class="text-muted">
                            <ul> Password Requirements:
                                <li class="mt-3">If the password does not meet the specified requirements, an error will
                                    be thrown.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </small></li>
                    <li class="ms-2 p-2"><small class="text-muted">
                            <ul>Server-Side Implementation:
                                <li class="mt-3">The authentication process is handled on the server-side using a POST
                                    route at
                                    "/login."</li>
                            </ul>
                        </small></li>
                    <li class="ms-2 p-2"><small class="text-muted">
                            <ul>User Lookup:
                                <li class="mt-3">The server queries the database to find a user with the provided
                                    username.</li>
                                <li class="mt-3">If no user is found, an error message is stored in the flash messaging
                                    system, and
                                    the user is redirected.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </small></li>
                    <li class="ms-2 p-2"><small class="text-muted">
                            <ul>Successful Authentication:
                                <li class="mt-3">If the passwords match, the user is considered authenticated.</li>
                                <li class="mt-3">The user's unique identifier (user._id) is stored in the session.</li>
                                <li class="mt-3">A success message is stored in the flash messaging system, welcoming
                                    the user back.
                                </li>
                                <li class="mt-3">The user is redirected to the "/auth" route.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </small></li>

                </ul>
            </div>
            <form action="/login" method="POST" class="form">
                <p class="form-title">Sign in to your account</p>
                <div class="input-container">
                    <input name="username" placeholder="Enter Username" type="text">
                    <span>
                        <svg stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                            <path
                                d="M16 12a4 4 0 10-8 0 4 4 0 008 0zm0 0v1.5a2.5 2.5 0 005 0V12a9 9 0 10-9 9m4.5-1.206a8.959 8.959 0 01-4.5 1.207"
                                stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                        </svg>
                    </span>
                </div>
                <div class="input-container">
                    <input name="password" id="password" placeholder="Enter password" type="password">

                    <span>
                        <svg id="eye" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
                            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                            <path d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round"
                                stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                            <path
                                d="M2.458 12C3.732 7.943 7.523 5 12 5c4.478 0 8.268 2.943 9.542 7-1.274 4.057-5.064 7-9.542 7-4.477 0-8.268-2.943-9.542-7z"
                                stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                        </svg>
                    </span>
                </div>
                <button class="submit" type="submit">
                    Sign in
                </button>


            </form>

        </div>


        <script>
            const password = document.getElementById('password')
            const eye = document.getElementById('eye')
            eye.onclick = function () {
                if (password.type == "password") {
                    password.type = "text";
                } else {
                    password.type = "password"
                }
            }
        </script>

        <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
            integrity="sha384-MrcW6ZMFYlzcLA8Nl+NtUVF0sA7MsXsP1UyJoMp4YLEuNSfAP+JcXn/tWtIaxVXM"
            crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</body>

</html>